{
  "texts": [
    "The dataset covers various regions of the Moon, including the nearside and the farside, and different types of terrain, such as mare, highlands, and polar areas.",
    "The dataset is divided into 24 subsets, each contains 83 or 84 images, for cross-validation.",
    "Cross-validation is a technique that splits the dataset into multiple subsets and evaluates the performance of the algorithm on each subset, using the rest of the data for training.",
    "This helps to reduce the bias and variance of the evaluation and to estimate the generalization ability of the algorithm.",
    "Different types of difficulties present in the image for accurately identifying their features:"
  ]
}